{{en-noun}}

# Male servant.
## {{context|now|_|rare}} A male [[servant]], in general senses. {{defdate|from 14th c.}}
## {{context|now|_|historical|offensive}} A non-white male [[servant]], as used especially by whites in a colonial settlement etc. {{defdate|from 17th c.}}
##: ''When the 'dipenda' (independence movement) in Belgian Congo turned violent, the white colonisers' often materially privileged black domestic '''boys''' were mistrusted and often abused as collaborators.''
